// ── How setState reaches BuildOwner ─────────────────
// State.setState(fn)
//   → fn();                          // mutate state
//   → _element.markNeedsBuild();     // mark this element dirty
//   → BuildOwner.scheduleBuildFor()  // queues the element
//   → SchedulerBinding.scheduleFrame() // ask for vsync
// next frame:
//   → BuildOwner.buildScope()        // walks dirty list, calls build()

// ── How a RenderObject change reaches PipelineOwner ─
// renderObject.markNeedsLayout()
//   → PipelineOwner.requestVisualUpdate()
//   → SchedulerBinding.scheduleFrame()
// next frame:
//   → PipelineOwner.flushLayout()    // recompute sizes
